# Agent Instructions

Use indexed code intelligence before broad grep or guessing.

Project index manifest:

- `.agent-index/agent-index.yaml`

Project skills:

- `.agents/skills/agent-index-router`
- `.agents/skills/agent-index-workspace`
- `.agents/skills/agent-index-lifecycle`

Rules:

- Use project-level skills under `.agents/skills`.
- Use `.agent-index/bin/agent-index` on POSIX or `.agent-index\bin\agent-index.cmd` on Windows for workspace and lifecycle commands.
- For initial workspace setup, use `agent-index workspace init`.
- Do not run workspace manifest update and repo exclude maintenance in parallel.
- Use lifecycle skills for setup, refresh, validation, repair, and provider changes.
- Use usage skills for daily retrieval and analysis.
- For cleanup of generated project-local index assets, use `agent-index clean`.
- Do not run bare `gitnexus` or bare `npx gitnexus`; use `agent-index provider gitnexus`.
- Do not create repo-local `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, or `.claude/skills/...` from GitNexus.
- Project workspace/lifecycle commands maintain child repo `.git/info/exclude` entries for local index directories such as `.codegraph/`, `.gitnexus/`, and `.understand-anything/`.
